node.text: Celebrating our greatest blessing, Princess Bolt 💕

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Kasi J. Bennett on August 21, 2021 tagging @usainbolt. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
Today we celebrate this one of a kind soul. There aren’t enough words to describe just how awesome life is with you and our little… well BIG tribe! ⚡️Bolt party of five we seh! ⚡️You mean the universe to us and we love you world without end! Today and everyday we honour you, my favourite parrie for life and my forever love!!!

Happpppyyyyyy Birthdayyyyyy baby!
Love you so much Big Daddy!!! ❤️❤️❤️

⚡️⚡️⚡️
Happy Father’s Day to my forever love! @usainbolt 
You are the rock of this family and the greatest daddy to our little ones. We love you world without end! 💛

node.text:
On August 21, 1986, the world welcomed a future legend. He would go on to become the world’s fastest man and achieve the seemingly unattainable. He captured the hearts of not only his fans but a one, Kasi Bennett. They would then have the most beautiful child out of pure love, Olympia Bolt. And thus began his greatest journey yet...

Happy birthday  to the man I am blessed to call my love. Olympia has the the world’s greatest daddy. The way you love us is otherworldly and I hope we made this day the most memorable birthday you’ve ever had! We love you so much my baby. I won’t do much writing (after that hella long letter this morning) but know that you are God-blessed and high favoured. I love you baby. My king forever ❤️
